cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.AR, cs.DC, cs.MM

This paper discusses the improvement of TCP communication performance in mobile satellite and terrestrial networks, which involves network infrastructure, communication protocols, and mobility events. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also mentions the use of Mobile IP (MIP) and Host Identity Protocol (HIP), which are related to cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses the periodic variations in communication properties and coverage, which are related to cs.AR (Hardware Architecture). Additionally, the paper mentions the implementation of TCP as a separate component in an operating system, which is related to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the use of multi-radios' communication, which is related to cs.MM (Multimedia).
